Saddam Hussain accused Kuwait and the UAE of flooding the oil market and driving  prices down, costing Iraq $14 billion; Kuwait of stealing oil from Iraqi border wells; and  Persian Gulf Arab states of conspiring with the US and Israel to weaken Iraq.
Kuwait  suggested Iraq wanted to eliminate Iran-Iraq War debts.
The US announced US-UAE  exercises in the Persian Gulf July 24th.
Kuwait and the UAE agreed to a halt in  overproduction.
By July 31st, Iraq had 100,000 troops on Kuwait's border.
Iraq pulled  out of talks with Kuwait in Jidda August 1st.
Iraqi tank-led troops invaded Kuwait at 2am  August 2nd, and seized the palace and government buildings. 
